Module org.nasdanika.resources
Package org.nasdanika.resources

Interface Resource<E>

Type Parameters:
E - Element type for the parent container.
All Known Subinterfaces:
BinaryContainer, BinaryEntity, BinaryEntityContainer, BinaryResource, Container<E>, Entity<T,E>, EntityContainer<C,E>, ResourceContainer<E>, TypedEntity<T>, TypedEntityContainer<T>, TypedResource<T>
All Known Implementing Classes:
BinaryContainerImpl, ContainerFilter, EphemeralBinaryEntity, EphemeralBinaryEntityContainer, EphemeralEntity, EphemeralEntityContainer, FileSystemContainer, FileSystemEntity, FileSystemResource, MapContainer
public interface Resource<E>
Resource typically represents something with a lifespan longer than the JVM. It is uniquely identified by its name within its container and its path within the root container. The resource path separator is ``/``.
Author:
Pavel

    • copy

      void copy(Container<? super E> container, String path, ProgressMonitor monitor)
      Copies the resource to the target container under a given path.
      Parameters:
      container - Target container, may be the same container.
      path - Path to copy the resource to.
      monitor - Parent progress monitor, the resource splits the monitor and takes size() ticks.

    • move

      void move(Container<? super E> container, String path, ProgressMonitor monitor)
      Moves the resource to the target container under a given path. Equivalent to copying and then deleting.
      Parameters:
      container - Target container.
      path - Path to move the resource to.
      monitor - Parent progress monitor, the resource splits the monitor and takes 2*size() ticks - one size for reading and one for writing.

    • getDigest

      default String getDigest()
      Returns:
      Resource digest. Entities compute state digest, e.g. SHA256 digest of file contents. Containers derive digest value from their children digests.

    • getTimestamp

      default long getTimestamp()
      Returns:
      Time when this resource was last modified, -1 if unknown. For containers modification means a change in the list of children, not necessarily change in the children's state.
